            Dholak<br> The dholak is a two-headed hand-drum from the Indian subcontinent.<br> It may have traditional cotton rope lacing, screw-turnbuckle tensioning or both combined: <br>in the first case steel rings are used for tuning or pegs are twisted
            inside the laces.<br>

